@Wadeck last time I looked at self-closing script tag, it wasn't supported by all web browsers. I know, makes no sense (html != xml), but just to be sure, did you test it?
First comment about that I can find is from 2013... but basically it would be because script can have a src and code in its body. So the closing tag seems to be mandatory.
This might also apply to div you have on line 50 as well.

